TASK_ID=69
TASK_TITLE=Charmbracelet luxury upgrade for doey CLI
TASK_STATUS=in_progress
TASK_CREATED=1774965403
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Comprehensive upgrade of the doey CLI command using Charmbracelet tools (gum, lipgloss, glamour, etc.) to create a premium, polished terminal experience. This covers the full doey command surface — startup, prompts, menus, output formatting, error messages, progress indicators, the wizard, doctor, status displays, and any other user-facing CLI interactions. Goal: make doey feel like a luxury product in the terminal.
TASK_TAGS=shell,tui,install
TASK_TEAM=W1
TASK_LOG_1774965441=PROGRESS: Dispatched to Team 1 for implementation
TASK_UPDATED=1774967477
TASK_DECISION_LOG=1774965475:Manager W1 received task. Starting with research wave to audit all user-facing output in doey CLI before planning implementation.\n1774965529:W2 Wave 1: 4 parallel research workers. W2.1=doey.sh audit, W2.2=secondary scripts, W2.3=charmbracelet tools, W2.4=dependency/install strategy\n1774965747:Wave 1 research complete. Planning implementation in 3 phases: Phase 1 = foundation (gum helpers + install.sh + doctor), Phase 2 = high-impact surfaces (banner, menus, progress, tables), Phase 3 = error/status polish + secondary files.\n1774965809:Wave 2: Foundation. W1=doey.sh helpers, W2=install.sh+doctor, W3=install gum. Sequential doey.sh edits.\n1774965956:Wave 2 complete. Moving to Wave 3: high-impact surface upgrades in doey.sh (banners, menus, progress, tables). Single worker on doey.sh.\n1774965963:Wave 1 complete: 4/4 workers finished. All attachments delivered. W2.1=1009 lines, W2.2=551 lines, W2.3=285 lines, W2.4=310 lines. Proceeding to Wave 2: synthesis.\n1774966238:Wave 2 complete: consolidated report produced (261 lines). All 5 research questions answered with attachments.\n1774966403:Wave 4: Validation. W1=doctor+compat, W2=visual verification of gum output.\n1774966529:P0 feedback: current upgrade is too conservative. Wave 5 will be a deep pass converting ALL remaining echo/printf to gum. Focus areas: startup sequence, project selector, every prompt/error/status message.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W1.1: Research — audit all user-facing output in shell/doey.sh:done\n2:W1.2: Research — check gum/charmbracelet status & install.sh:done\n3:W1.3: Research — audit secondary shell files for user-facing output:done\n4:W2.1: Audit doey.sh user-facing interactions (lines, types, formats):pending\n5:W2.2: Audit info-panel.sh, install.sh, other shell/ scripts:pending\n6:W2.3: Charmbracelet tools inventory and mapping:pending\n7:W2.4: Dependency strategy, install-path impact, fallback plan:pending\n8:W1.1: Add gum helpers & HAS_GUM detection to doey.sh:done\n9:W1.2: Add gum check to install.sh and doctor:done\n10:W1.3: Install gum on dev system:done\n11:W2.1: Wave 2 — compile opportunity map + consolidated report from all 4 research outputs:pending\n12:W1.1: Upgrade doey.sh banners, menus, progress, doctor to use gum helpers:done\n13:W1.2: Upgrade pre-push-gate.sh with gum styling:done\n14:W1.3: Upgrade doey-render-task.sh with gum styling:done\n15:W1.4: Upgrade info-panel.sh with gum styling:done\n16:W1.1: Run doey doctor and full bash 3.2 compat test:pending\n17:W1.2: Run doey --help, doey list, doey version to verify gum output:pending\n18:W1.1: Deep luxury pass on doey.sh — startup sequence, project selector, ALL remaining plain output:done\n19:W1.2: Deep luxury pass on info-panel.sh — ALL sections must use gum:done\n20:W1.3: Deep luxury pass on pre-push-gate.sh and doey-render-task.sh — total coverage:done\n21:W1.4: Deep luxury pass on context-audit.sh and doey-task-helpers.sh:done
